{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2017}} {{Infobox person | name = Ernest Desjardins | image = ErnestDesjardins.jpg | image_size = 177px | alt = Ernest Desjardins | caption = Ernest Desjardins | other_names = | occupation = French geographer | birth_date = {{start-date|30 October 1823}} | death_date = {{Death-date and age|22 October 1886|30 October 1823|df=yes}} | birth_place = Noisy-sur-Oise | death_place = Paris }}
'''Antoine Émile Ernest Desjardins''' (30 September 1823, [[Noisy-sur-Oise]] – 22 October 1886, Paris) was a French historian, [[geographer]] and [[archaeologist]]. He was a younger brother of historian Abel Desjardins (1814–1886).
In 1856 he began teaching classes in Latin [[epigraphy]] at the [[Lycée Napoleon]] in Paris, and from 1861 taught courses in geography at the [[École Normale Supérieure]]. For several years he conducted archaeological research in Italy, [[Egypt]] and regions along the [[Danube]]. In 1875, he became a member of the [[Académie des Inscriptions et Belles-Lettres]].<ref name=SS>[http://cths.fr/an/prosopo.php?id=214 Desjardins, Ernest Émile Antoine] Sociétés savantes de France</ref><ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=RhhKAQAAMAAJ&pg=PA271&lpg=PA271&dq=%22Ernest+Desjardins%22+%22Noisy-sur-Oise%22&source=bl&ots=y72p15P2Oa&sig=uLDftCALx7bMZrdMY0ckC7JCLC8&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjQ_vyzopzKAhWCHT4KHe1aDwQ4ChDoAQgbMAA#v=onepage&q=%22Ernest%20Desjardins%22%20%22Noisy-sur-Oise%22&f=false Walford's Antiquarian, Volume 10] Google Books</ref> In 1886, he was appointed professor of epigraphy and Roman antiquities at the [[Collège de France]].<ref>[https://fr.wikisource.org/wiki/Auteur:Ernest_Desjardins Ernest Desjardins] fr. Wikisource</ref>
== Selected works == * ''Atlas geographique de l'Itali ancienne, : composé de sept cartes et d'un dictionnaire de tous les noms qui y sont contenus'', 1852 – Geographical atlas of ancient Italy. * ''Essai sur la topographie du Latium'', 1854 – Essay on the topography of [[Latium]]. * ''Le Pérou avant la conquête espagnole, d'après les principaux historiens originaux'', 1858 – [[Peru]] before the Spanish conquest, etc. * ''Publication des oeuvres complètes de Bartolomeo Borghesi'', 1861 – Publication on the complete works of [[Bartolomeo Borghesi]]. * ''Le grand Corneille, historien'', 1862 – On [[Pierre Corneille]]. * ''Aperçu historique sur les embouchures du Rhône, travaux anciens et modernes'', 1866 – Historical overview on the mouth of the [[Rhône River|Rhône]], ancient and modern works. * ''Les Juifs de Moldaviem'', 1867 – The Jews of [[Moldova]]. * ''Rapport sur les deux ouvrages de bibliographie américaine de M. Henri Harrisse'', 1867 – Report on two American bibliographical works of [[Henry Harrisse]]. * ''Géographie de la Gaule d'après la Tabel de Peutinger'', 1869 – Geography of Gaul according to the [[Peutinger Table]]. * ''Rhone et Danube. Nouvelles observations sur les fosses Mariennes et le canal du Bas-Rhone'', 1870. – The Rhône and Danube. New observations on the Fosses Mariennes and the Bas-Rhône canal. * ''Géographie historique et administrative de la Gaule romaine'', (with [[Auguste Longnon]]) 1876 – Historical and administrative geography of [[Roman Gaul]].<ref>[http://catalog.hathitrust.org/Search/Home?lookfor=%22Desjardins,Ernest,1823-1886.%22&type=author&inst= HathiTrust Digital Library] published works</ref>
