The [[Ketu (Benin)|state of Ketu]] is located in present-day [[Republic of Benin]].
In the [[Yoruba language]], the word ''oba'' means '''king''' or '''ruler'''. It is also common for the rulers of the various [[Yoruba people|Yoruba]] domains to have their own special titles. In Ketu the [[Oba (ruler)|Oba]] is referred to as the '''Aleketu of Ketu'''
