{{Infobox settlement |official_name = Shushekend / Shosh |native_name = |pushpin_map = Republic of Artsakh |pushpin_mapsize = 300 |subdivision_type = ''[[de jure]]'' Country |subdivision_name = {{flag|Azerbaijan}} |subdivision_type1 = ''de jure'' [[Administrative divisions of Azerbaijan|Rayon]] |subdivision_name1 = [[Khojali Rayon|Khojali]] |subdivision_type2 = ''[[de facto]]'' Country |subdivision_name2 = {{flag|Artsakh}} |subdivision_type3 = ''de facto'' [[Administrative divisions of the Republic of Artsakh|Province]] |subdivision_name3 = [[Askeran Region|Askeran]] |leader_title = |leader_name = |established_title = |established_date = |area_total_km2 = |area_footnotes = |population_as_of = |population_total = |population_density_km2 = auto |timezone = |utc_offset = +4 |timezone_DST = |utc_offset_DST = |coordinates = {{coord|39|46|12|N|46|47|05|E|region:{{xb|NKR}}|display=inline,title}} |elevation_m = |area_code = |website = }} '''Shushekend''' ({{lang-az|Şuşakənd}} '''Shushekend''', '''Shushikend''', also '''Şuşikənd'''; {{lang-hy|Շոշ}} '''Shosh''') is a village internationally recognized as part of [[Azerbaijan]] ([[Khojali Rayon]]), but currently controlled by the ''[[de facto]]'' independent unrecognized [[Republic of Artsakh]] ([[Askeran Region]]). There are two Armenian churches in the village, one in the village center, and S. Stepanos of 1655 CE in the cemetery.<ref>Mkrtchyan, Shahen. Historical-Architectural Monuments of Nagorno Karabagh. Yerevan, 1989. (''Շահեն Մկրտչյան, «Լեռնային Ղարաբաղի պատմաճարտարապետական հուշարձանները»'')</ref> Above the village on a rise in the north is a third church with adjacent cemetery and [[khachkar]]s.<ref>Mkrtchyan, Shahen. Historical-Architectural Monuments of Nagorno Karabagh. Yerevan, 1989. (''Շահեն Մկրտչյան, «Լեռնային Ղարաբաղի պատմաճարտարապետական հուշարձանները»'')</ref>
